## 🛡️ 1. Tier Quota Enforcement & Azure Credit Protection
To prevent your $100 Azure credit from being spammed, we will activate the unused `recordTokens` infrastructure in `gemini.ts` and connect it to the streaming handlers:

```mermaid
graph TD
    Request[User Prompt Request] --> Auth[Verify JWT & Fetch Tier Status]
    Auth --> CheckQuota{Is user token usage >= tier limit?}
    
    CheckQuota -->|Yes| Block[Return Quota Exceeded SSE Error]
    CheckQuota -->|No| Stream[Begin Streaming from Azure Model]
    
    Stream --> Accumulate[Accumulate response text length]
    Accumulate --> Record[At end of stream: Call recordTokens]
    Record --> Supabase[Update users.ai_tokens_used or users.byok_tokens_used]
```

### Flow Specifications:
* **Token Budget Limits**:
  - **Free Tier**: 50,000 monthly tokens. Using your system keys (on Azure) is capped strictly.
  - **Pro Tier**: 5,000,000 monthly tokens. Enforces limits to offset costs via their monthly subscription.
* **BYOK Support**:
  - If `customApiKey` is detected, token tracking will update the `byok_tokens_used` column instead of `ai_tokens_used`, and the limit checks will be bypassed completely since they are paying for their own tokens.

